comments.body:
this seems very manual, if it's really the only way to get the pid, maybe we can do a precompiled regex instead:
```C++
const std::string s{std::istreambuf_iterator<char>{sf}, {}};
static const std::regex re(R"(TracerPid:\s*(\d+))", std::regex::optimize);
if (std::smatch m; std::regex_search(s, m, re)) attached = std::stoul(m[1]) > 0;
```
or
```C++
static const std::regex re(R"(TracerPid:\s*(\d+))", std::regex::optimize);
for (std::string line; !attached && std::getline(sf, line);) {
    if (std::smatch m; std::regex_search(line, m, re)) attached = std::stoul(m[1]) > 0;
}
```

