comments.body:
I'd rather not go as heavy as regex here, but limited the scope of `name` & `pid`:
```C++
for (std::string name; status.good();
    // Skips to the beginning of next line using name as scratch buffer.
    std::getline(status, name)) {
    status >> name;
    if (name == "TracerPid:") {
        uint pid{0};
        status >> pid;
        attached = pid > 0;
        break;
    }
}
```

